wdi2-SL.IND.EMPL.ZS.def: Employment is defined as persons of working age who were engaged in any activity to produce goods or provide services for pay or profit, whether at work during the reference period or not at work due to temporary absence from a job, or to working-time arrangement. The industry sector consists of mining and quarrying, manufacturing, construction, and public utilities (electricity, gas, and water), in accordance with divisions 2-5 (ISIC 2) or categories C-F (ISIC 3) or categories B-F (ISIC 4).
wdi2-SL.IND.EMPL.ZS.name: Employment in industry
wdi2-SL.IND.EMPL.ZS.source: International Labour Organization, ILOSTAT database. Data retrieved on January 29, 2021.
